Configuration steps on ubuntu 16.04 LTS
1. Install node 12
    curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_12.x | sudo -E bash - 
	sudo apt-get install -y nodejs

2. Check node and npm version 
    node –v 
    npm –v 

3. Create  package.json with 
			sudo npm init 

4. Install socket.io with npm 
	npm install  socket.io 
 
5. Install Expressjs 
	sudo npm install --save express@4.15.2 

6 . Redis Install
    sudo apt install redis-server
	sudo a2enmod proxy proxy_balancer proxy_wstunnel proxy_http
    	sudo npm install redis
	sudo npm install redis –save
	redis-server –version 

7. Update Apache vhost / Create reverse proxy for apache & nodejs   
	check Nodejs-Expressjs-setup file

8. Create indexjs for server entry

9. Run 
	nohup node redis-pusher.js &
	nohup node redis.js & 
			
10. ps -ef|grep node

11.

 




 



 

